description.en:
The Building Material Performance ontology is created to enrich 
building information models with highly aggregated information with respect to material information modelling and material simulation.

BMP classifies construction materials based on categories, types and property groups. Each property group describes parameters to be used as input values for simulation works.

comment.en: A property is an inherent or acquired feature of an item and cannot be part of several property sets.
The Layer Function class is used to give a first-time identification of building components, such as a layer, in building models.
Service life time of a material or a product
Material Category class is used to describe material categories in a higher aggregated level.
Material Types class is used to describe material typologies and sub typologies in low aggregated level.
Material class is used to describe a material as a non-living entity that manifest properties that can be measured or characterised.
